extensionName.description: Please keep in mind that these strings had to be approved by the Google Brand Features Team. Be sure to make clear that this extension is *FOR* Google Calendar and not *BY* Google. Also, it was explicitly stated, that the phrase 'Google Calendar' should be localized just as it is on the localized versions of the Google Calendar UI.

gdata.migration.description.message: Tjenesten Google Kalender har registreret, at du har eksisterende kalendere, som ikke er i stand til at skrive til kalendere hos Google Kalender. Hvis du vil opgradere nogen af disse kalendere, så vælg dem nedenfor.

gdata.wizard.session.description.message: Vælg en eksisterende session, eller indtast en mailadresse, for at oprette en ny session. Du skal kun bruge én session pr. konto.

gdata.wizard.calendars.description.message: Vælg de kalendere og lister over opgaver, du vil abonnere på.

gdata.wizard.nextstep.description.message: Fortsæt til næste trin for at indstille dine kalendere.

busyTitle.description: Events with only free/busy access don't have a title, they will use this title instead. The calendar name is used as a parameter, since its often named after the person whose calendar you are viewing.
